# STEP 1 — HTTP apex → HTTPS apex
http://sevenangelsmassage.com/* https://sevenangelsmassage.com/:splat 301!

# STEP 2 — HTTPS apex → HTTPS www
https://sevenangelsmassage.com/* https://www.sevenangelsmassage.com/:splat 301!

# STEP 3 — Clean /home on www
https://www.sevenangelsmassage.com/home  https://www.sevenangelsmassage.com 301!
https://www.sevenangelsmassage.com/home/ https://www.sevenangelsmassage.com 301!

# 4) Worker-down fallback (only applies when Pages/Netlify is serving)
#    Put LAST so it doesn't override the canonical redirects above.
#    NOTE: This is mainly for your Pages/WWW scenario.
#    If this repo is serving WWW, it can redirect to origin.
#    If this repo is serving apex, you probably *don't* want this to override.
#    So keep it scoped (see below).
https://www.sevenangelsmassage.com/*  https://origin.sevenangelsmassage.com/:splat  302
https://origin.sevenangelsmassage.com/home  https://origin.sevenangelsmassage.com 301!
https://origin.sevenangelsmassage.com/home/  https://origin.sevenangelsmassage.com 301!
